NO (2) from United States District Court for the Central District of California\n(Western Division- Los Angeles) Case Number 2:24-mj-05703 (zstd) (Entered: 09/25/2024)\n10/07/2024 10 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Paulette Pagan appearing for Jeandiel Serrano (2) (zstd) (Entered: 10/07/2024)\n10/08/2024 Arrest of JEANDIEL SERRRANO (2) ON 9/18/2024 in Los Angeles, CA. (ztl) (Entered: 10/08/2024)\n10/08/2024 12 Arrest Warrant Returned Executed on 9/18/2024 as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (2). (ztl) (Entered: 10/08/2024)\n10/08/2024 ORAL MOTION to Unseal Case by USA as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (2). (zltp) (Entered: 10/09/2024)\n10/08/2024 ORAL MOTION for Temporary Detention by USA as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (2). (zltp) (Entered: 10/09/2024)\n10/08/2024 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Zia M. Faruqui: Return on Arrest Warrant/Initial Appearance/Arraignment as\nto JEANDIEL SERRANO (2) as to Count 1,2 held on 10/8/2024. Plea of Not Guilty entered as to all counts. The Court advised the\nGovernment of its Due Process Obligations under Rule 5(f). Oral Motion by the Government to Unseal Case as to JEANDIEL SERRANO\n(2); heard and granted. Oral Motion by the Government for Temporary Detention as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (2); heard and granted.\nDetention Hearing set for 10/10/2024 at 11:00 AM in Courtroom 6- In Person before Magistrate Judge G. Michael Harvey. Status\nConference set for 10/23/2024 at 3:30 PM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Bond Status of Defendant:\nDefendant held without Bond; Court Reporter: FTR-GOLD; FTR Time Frame: CTRM 4: [3:46:06 - 4:03:05]; Defense Attorney: Paulette\nPagan; US Attorney: Kevin L. Rosenberg; Pretrial Officer: Da'Shanta Valentine-Lewis. (zltp) (Entered: 10/09/2024)\n10/08/2024 Case unsealed as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (2). (zltp) (Entered: 10/09/2024)\n10/08/2024 MINUTE ORDER as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (2): As required by Rule 5(f), the United States is ordered to produce all exculpatory\nevidence to the defendant pursuant to Brady v. Maryland and its progeny. Not doing so in a timely manner may result in sanctions,\nincluding exclusion of evidence, adverse jury instructions, dismissal of charges and contempt proceedings. Signed by Magistrate Judge\nZia M. Faruqui on 10/8/2024. (znjb) (Entered: 10/10/2024)\n10/09/2024 13 MEMORANDUM in Support of Pretrial Detention by USA as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (Attachments: # 1 Exhibit Order of Detention, #\n2 Exhibit Order of Detention)(Rosenberg, Kevin) Modified text on 10/10/2024 (zstd). (Entered: 10/09/2024)\n10/10/2024 MINUTE ORDER as to JEANDIEL SERRANO rescheduling status hearing: The parties are ORDERED to appear for a status hearing on\nOCTOBER 22, 2024 at 11:30 AM ET in Courtroom 28A. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 10/10/2024. (lcckk3) (Entered:\n10/10/2024)\n10/10/2024 14 ORDER as to JEANDIEL SERRANO confirming Government's disclosure obligations under Brady v. Maryland. Signed by Judge Colleen\nKollar-Kotelly on 10/10/2024. (lcckk3) (Entered: 10/10/2024)\n10/10/2024 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge G. Michael Harvey: Status Hearing as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (2) held on\n10/10/2024. Case called for Detention Hearing but not held. Bond Status of Defendant: Defendant held without Bond; Court Reporter:\nFTR-GOLD; FTR Time Frame: CTRM 6: [11:12:37 - 11:26:52]; Defense Attorney: Paulette Pagan; US Attorney: Kevin L. Rosenberg;\nPretrial Officer: Shania Fenell. (zltp) (Entered: 10/11/2024)\n10/16/2024 15 Consent MOTION for Protective Order by USA as to JEANDIEL SERRANO. (Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered: 10/16/2024)\n10/17/2024 16 PROTECTIVE ORDER as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (2). Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 10/17/2024. (lcckk3) (zdot).\n(Entered: 10/17/2024)\n10/18/2024 17 MOTION to Revoke Detention Order by JEANDIEL SERRANO. (Attachments: # 1 Text of Proposed Order Proposed Order, # 2 Exhibit\nExhibit A, # 3 Exhibit EXHIBIT B)(Pagan, Paulette) (Entered: 10/18/2024)\n10/18/2024 18 RESPONSE by USA as to JEANDIEL SERRANO re 17 MOTION to Revoke Detention Order (Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered: 10/18/2024)\n10/18/2024 19 ORDER denying 17 Motion to Revoke as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (2). Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 10/18/2024. (lcckk3)\n(Entered: 10/18/2024)\n10/18/2024 20 MEMORANDUM OPINION accompanying 19 ORDER as to JEANDIEL SERRANO. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on\n10/18/2024. (lcckk3) (Entered: 10/18/2024)\n10/21/2024 MINUTE ORDER as to JEANDIEL SERRANO rescheduling status hearing: The parties are ORDERED to appear for a status hearing on\nOCTOBER 22, 2024 at 1:30 PM ET in Courtroom 28A. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 10/21/2024. (lcckk3) (Entered:\n10/21/2024)\n10/21/2024 Set/Reset Hearings as to JEANDIEL SERRANO: Status Conference set for 10/22/2024 at 1:30 PM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before\nJudge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. (dot) (Entered: 10/21/2024)\n10/22/2024 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly:Status Conference as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (02) held on\n10/22/2024. Parties Updated The Court In Regards To Discovery And Request Continuance. Further Status Conference set for 1/9/2025 at\n9:30 AM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. With The Consent Of The Defendant, Speedy Trial Time Is\nExcluded 10/08/2024 - 01/09/2025 In The Interest Of Justice (XT). Bond Status of Defendant: COMMITTED/COMMITMENT ISSUED;\nCourt Reporter: LORRAINE HERMAN; Defense Attorney: PAULETTE PAGAN; US Attorney: KEVIN ROSENBERG; (mac) (Entered:\n10/22/2024)\n10/22/2024 MINUTE ORDER as to JEANDIEL SERRANO (2): The Court held a status hearing in this matter on October 22, 2024. Defendant, his\ncounsel, the Government, and a court reporter were present in person. The parties both reported to the Court that an initial discovery\nproduction had been delivered and that additional discovery was forthcoming. The parties further reported that discovery in this matter\nwould be technically complex and that the parties are currently engaged in seeking a resolution of this matter short of trial. Both\nDefendant and the Government requested roughly 60 days to produce and review discovery and continue plea negotiations. The Court\nORDERS the parties to appear for a status hearing at 9:30 AM ET on JANUUARY 9, 2025 in Courtroom 28A. In the event the parties\nreach an agreement on a pretrial resolution before that status hearing, they shall inform the Court via joint status report.\n\nFinally, the Court discussed with Defendant his Speedy Trial Act rights. Defendant consented to the exclusion of time between October 8,\n2024 (the date of his initial appearance in this District) and January 9, 2025 (the date of his next status hearing). The Court finds that such\nexclusion is warranted because the ends of justice served by allowing the parties time to review the complex discovery in this matter and\nengage in negotiations for a resolution short of trial outweigh the interest of the public and Defendant in a speedy trial. Taking into\naccount this exclusion, the Court calculates that Defendant's 70-day deadline is March 20, 2025 and that his 90-day deadline is April 9,\n2025. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 10/22/2024. (lcckk3) (Entered: 10/22/2024)\n10/28/2024 21 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Scott Armstrong appearing for MALONE LAM (1) (zstd) (Entered: 10/28/2024)\n10/30/2024 22 MOTION for Protective Order by USA as to MALONE LAM (1). (Attachments: # 1 Text of Proposed Order)(zstd) (Entered: 10/30/2024)\n11/01/2024 23 Arrest Warrant Returned Executed on 9/18/2024 as to MALONE LAM (1). (zltp) (Entered: 11/01/2024)\n11/01/2024 Arrest of MALONE LAM (1) in Florida. (zltp) (Entered: 11/01/2024)\n11/01/2024 ORAL MOTION to Unseal Case by USA as to MALONE LAM (1). (zltp) (Entered: 11/04/2024)\n11/01/2024 ORAL MOTION for Speedy Trial by USA as to MALONE LAM (1). (zltp) (Entered: 11/04/2024)\n11/01/2024 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Moxila A. Upadhyaya: Return on Arrest Warrant/Initial\nAppearance/Arraignment as to MALONE LAM (1) as to Count 1,2 held on 11/1/2024. Plea of Not Guilty entered as to all counts. The\nCourt advised the Government of its Due Process Obligations under Rule 5(f). Oral Motion by the Government to Unseal Case as to\nMALONE LAM (1); heard and granted. Notice of Right to Consular Notification given to Defendant. Oral Motion by the Government for\nSpeedy Trial as to MALONE LAM (1); heard and granted. Speedy Trial Excluded from 11/1/2024 to 1/9/2025 in the Interest of Justice\n(XT). Status Conference set for 1/9/2025 at 9:30 AM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Bond Status of\nDefendant: Defendant held without Bond; Court Reporter: FTR-GOLD; FTR Time Frame: CTRM 5: [1:14:26 - 1:23:45]; Defense\nAttorney: Scott Armstrong; US Attorney: Kevin Rosenberg; Pretrial Officer: Lakeisha Forbes. (zltp) (Entered: 11/04/2024)\n11/01/2024 Case unsealed as to MALONE LAM (1). (zltp) (Entered: 11/04/2024)\n11/05/2024 24 PROTECTIVE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1). Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 11/1/2024. (lcckk3) (Entered: 11/05/2024)\n11/05/2024 25 ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1) confirming Government's disclosure obligations under Brady v. Maryland. Signed by Judge Colleen\nKollar-Kotelly on 11/5/2024. (lcckk3) (Entered: 11/05/2024)\n11/05/2024 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1): Defendant Lam, Defense Counsel, and the Government are ORDERED to appear for a\nstatus hearing at 10:00 AM ET on NOVEMBER 14, 2024 in Courtroom 28A. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 11/5/2024.\n(lcckk3) (Entered: 11/05/2024)\n11/05/2024 26 MOTION for Leave to Appear Pro Hac Vice Patrick Queenan Filing fee $ 100, receipt number DCDC-11280730. Fee Status: Fee Paid. by\nMALONE LAM as to MALONE LAM. (Attachments: # 1 Declaration of Patrick J. Queenan)(Armstrong, Scott) Modified to remove\nincorrect linked defendant on 11/5/2024 (zstd). (Entered: 11/05/2024)\n11/05/2024 Set/Reset Hearings as to MALONE LAM (1): Status Conference set for 11/14/2024 at 10:00 AM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before\nJudge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. (dot) (Entered: 11/05/2024)\n11/05/2024 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1) denying without prejudice 26 Motion for Leave to Appear Pro Hac Vice of Attorney Patrick\nQueenan. Mr. Queenan is directed to refile and provide both an office address and telephone number as required by LCrR 44.1(c)(2). Mr.\nQueenan is further directed to include a declaration certifying his familiarity with this Court's local rules. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-\nKotelly on 11/5/2024. (lcckk3) (Entered: 11/05/2024)\n11/12/2024 27 Second MOTION for Leave to Appear Pro Hac Vice Patrick J. Queenan Filing fee $ 100, receipt number DCDC-11292347. Fee Status:\nFee Paid. by MALONE LAM. (Attachments: # 1 Declaration)(Armstrong, Scott) Modified to remove incorrect linked defendant on\n11/12/2024 (zstd). (Entered: 11/12/2024)\n11/12/2024 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1)granting 27 Motion for Leave to Appear Pro Hac Vice of Patrick Queenan. Counsel should\nregister for e-filing via PACER and file a notice of appearance pursuant to LCrR 44.5(a). Click for instructions. Signed by Judge\nColleen Kollar-Kotelly on 11/12/2024. (lcckk3) (Entered: 11/12/2024)\n11/12/2024 28 TRANSCRIPT OF RETURN ON INDICTMENT/INITIAL APPEARANCE/ARRAIGNMENT in case as to MALONE LAM before\nMagistrate Judge Moxila A. Upadhyaya held on November 1, 2024; Page Numbers: 1-11. Date of Issuance: November 12, 2024. Court\nReporter/Transcriber Lisa Edwards. Telephone number (202) 354-3269. Transcripts may be ordered by submitting the Transcript Order\nForm\n\nFor the first 90 days after this filing date, the transcript may be viewed at the courthouse at a public terminal or purchased from the court\nreporter referenced above. After 90 days, the transcript may be accessed via PACER. Other transcript formats, (multi-page, condensed, CD\nor ASCII) may be purchased from the court reporter.\n\nNOTICE RE REDACTION OF TRANSCRIPTS: The parties have twenty-one days to file with the court and the court reporter any\nrequest to redact personal identifiers from this transcript. If no such requests are filed, the transcript will be made available to the public\nvia PACER without redaction after 90 days. The policy, which includes the five personal identifiers specifically covered, is located on our\nwebsite at www.dcd.uscourts.gov.\n\nRedaction Request due 12/3/2024. Redacted Transcript Deadline set for 12/13/2024. Release of Transcript Restriction set for 2/10/2025.\n(Edwards, Lisa) (Entered: 11/12/2024)\n11/13/2024 29 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Patrick Queenan appearing for MALONE LAM (Queenan, Patrick) (Entered: 11/13/2024)\n11/14/2024 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1): The Court held a status hearing in this matter on November 14, 2024. Defendant, his\ncounsel, the Government, and a court reporter were present in person. The parties both reported to the Court that an initial discovery\nproduction had been delivered and that additional discovery was forthcoming. Defendant reported that he has not yet had the opportunity\nto view all of the Government's productions and that the parties are coordinating methods for production. Defendant further reported that\nhe intends to move forward to trial. The Court ORDERS the parties to appear for a status hearing in Courtroom 28A at 9:30 AM ET on\nJANUARY 9, 2025, the date of the next status hearing scheduled for Defendant's co-defendant JEANDIEL SERRANO (2). The Court\nwill separately distribute to the parties a pretrial scheduling template for their review in advance of the upcoming hearing.\n\nThe Government also reported that it will coordinate with Defendant Lams new counsel regarding consular notification.\n\nFinally, the Court discussed with Defendant Lam his Speedy Trial Act rights. Defendant asserted his right to a speedy trial. Magistrate\nJudge Moxila A. Upadhyaya previously overruled Defendant Lam's request not to exclude time under the Speedy Trial Act and entered an\nends-of-justice continuance until January 9, 2025, the date of the next status hearing. See Min. Entry, Nov. 1, 2024. That exclusion remains\nin effect. Taking into account this exclusion, the Court calculates that Defendant Lam's 70-day deadline is March 20, 2025 and that his 90-\nday deadline is April 9, 2025. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 11/14/2024. (lcckk3) (Entered: 11/14/2024)\n11/14/2024 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly: Status Conference as to MALONE LAM (1) held on 11/14/2024.\nExcludable started as to MALONE LAM. Speedy Trial (XT) is tolled in the Interest of Justice from 11/14/2024 to 1/9/2025. Status\nConference set for 1/9/2025 at 9:30 AM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Bond Status of Defendant:\nCommitted/Commitment Issued; Court Reporter: Lisa Edwards; Defense Attorney: Scott Armstrong and Patrick Queenan; US Attorney:\nKevin L. Rosenberg. (dot) (Entered: 11/14/2024)\n01/01/2025 36 Consent MOTION to Continue Status Conference, Consent MOTION to Vacate Status Conference by USA as to MALONE LAM,\nJEANDIEL SERRANO. (Attachments: # 1 Text of Proposed Order Proposed Order)(Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered: 01/01/2025)\n01/02/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1) and JEANDIEL SERRANO (2): For good cause shown, the Government's 36 Consent\nMotion to Vacate and Continue Status Conference is GRANTED. The hearing previously set for January 9, 2025, is CONTINUED to\nFebruary 19, 2025, at 1:00 p.m. ET, in Courtroom 28-A, to allow additional time for Defendants Lam (1) and Serrano (2) and their\ncounsel to review discovery. On or before January 10, 2025, counsel for Defendants Lam (1) and Serrano (2) shall each file a written\nwaiver, personally signed by each defendant, indicating whether each defendant consents to excluding time between January 9, 2025, and\nFebruary 19, 2025, from the computation of time under the Speedy Trial Act. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 1/2/2025.\n(lcckk1) (Entered: 01/02/2025)\n01/02/2025 Set/Reset Deadlines as to MALONE LAM (1), JEANDIEL SERRANO (2): Written waiver excluding time under STA due by 1/10/2025.\n(zdrf) (Entered: 01/02/2025)\n01/09/2025 37 NOTICE Defendant Malone Lam's Speedy Trial Waiver and Consent to Exclude Time Under the Speedy Trial Act by MALONE LAM\n(Queenan, Patrick) (Entered: 01/09/2025)\n02/14/2025 38 Consent MOTION to Vacate Status Hearing, Consent MOTION to Continue Status Hearing by USA as to MALONE LAM, JEANDIEL\nSERRANO. (Attachments: # 1 Text of Proposed Order Proposed Order)(Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered: 02/14/2025)\n02/18/2025 39 ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1), JEANDIEL SERRANO (2) granting 38 Motion to Vacate and Continue. See Order for details. Signed\nby Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 2/18/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 02/18/2025)\n02/18/2025 Set/Reset Deadlines as to MALONE LAM (1), JEANDIEL SERRANO (2): Terminate Hearings as to MALONE LAM, JEANDIEL\nSERRANO. Waiver of Speedy Trial notices due by 2/28/2025. (dot) (Entered: 02/18/2025)\n02/20/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1), JEANDIEL SERRANO (2): The parties shall appear for a status hearing at 10:00 AM ET\non MARCH 7, 2025 in Courtroom 28A. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 2/20/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 02/20/2025)\n02/20/2025 Set/Reset Hearings as to MALONE LAM (1), JEANDIEL SERRANO (2): Status Conference set for 3/7/2025 at 10:00 AM in Courtroom\n28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. (dot) (Entered: 02/21/2025)\n03/06/2025 40 NOTICE relating to March 7, 2025 Status Conference by MALONE LAM (Armstrong, Scott) (Entered: 03/06/2025)\n03/06/2025 41 RESPONSE by USA as to MALONE LAM re 40 Notice (Other) (Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered: 03/06/2025)\n03/06/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1): By prior order, the Court continued a status conference in this matter from January 9, 2025\nto February 19, 2025. Min. Order (Jan. 2, 2025). In the 36 Consent Motion requesting that continuance, counsel represented that\nDefendant Lam consented to the exclusion of Speedy Trial time between those dates. The Court ordered Lam to file a signed waiver\nmemorializing that consent. Min. Order (Jan. 2, 2025). Lam has filed that waiver. Notice, ECF No. 37 .\n\nThe Court finds that the exclusion of time between January 9, 2025 and February 19, 2025 is in the interests of justice and outweighs\nLam's and the public's interest in a speedy trial because such exclusion allowed Lam and his counsel additional time to review discovery.\nThe Court calculates that, taking into account this exclusion, Lam's 70-day deadline is April 30, 2025 and his 90-day deadline is May 20,\n2025. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 3/6/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 03/06/2025)\n03/07/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly: Status Conference as to MALONE LAM (1) held on 3/7/2025.\nExcludable started as to MALONE LAM. Speedy Trial (XT) is tolled in the Interest of Justice, 2/19/2025 to 3/7/2025 and 3/7/2025 to\n5/12/2025. Status Conference set for 5/12/2025 at 1:30 PM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Jury Trial\nset for 10/6/2025 at 9:00 AM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Bond Status of Defendant:\nCOMMITTED/COMMITMENT ISSUED; Court Reporter: Tammy Nestor; Defense Attorney: Patrick Queenan and Scott Armstrong; US\nAttorney: Kevin L. Rosenberg. (dot) (Entered: 03/07/2025)\n03/07/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1): The Court held a status hearing in this matter on March 7, 2025. Defendant, his counsel, the\nGovernment, and a court reporter were present in person. The Court discussed the posture of this case with the parties. Defense counsel\nreported that Defendant had received, reviewed, and rejected a plea offer from the Government. This matter is scheduled for trial on\nOCTOBER 6, 2025.\nThe Court will distribute to the parties a pretrial scheduling template. The Court ORDERS that the parties file a proposed scheduling order\nfollowing this template on or before MARCH 26, 2025. The Court ORDERS that the parties file a supplemental proposed scheduling\norder addressing any contemplated evidentiary hearings on or before MAY 7, 2025. The Court further ORDERS that the parties appear for\na status hearing at 1:30 PM ET on MAY 12, 2025 in Courtroom 28A, at which time the parties should be prepared to put the terms of the\nrejected plea offer on the record.\n\nFinally, the Court discussed with Defendant Lam his Speedy Trial Act rights. Defendant confirmed his consent to tolling Speedy Trial time\nbetween February 19, 2025 and March 7, 2025. See 38 Consent Motion. Defendant further consented to tolling time between March 7,\n2025 and May 12, 2025, the date of his next status hearing. The Court finds that such exclusion is in the interests of justice and outweighs\nthe interests of Defendant and the community in a speedy trial because it will allow Defendant and his counsel to conduct motions practice\nand prepare for trial. Taking into account this exclusion, the Court calculates that Defendant Lam's 70-day deadline is July 21, 2025 and\nthat his 90-day deadline is August 10, 2025. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 3/7/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 03/07/2025)\n03/26/2025 42 NOTICE of Proposed Order Government's Proposed Scheduling Order by USA as to MALONE LAM (Attachments: # 1 Text of Proposed\nOrder Proposed Scheduling Order)(Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered: 03/26/2025)\n03/26/2025 43 NOTICE regarding Mr. Lam's Proposed Scheduling Order by MALONE LAM as to MALONE LAM (Attachments: # 1 Exhibit Proposed\nScheduling Order of Malone Lam)(Armstrong, Scott) Modified to remove incorrect linked defendant on 3/26/2025 (zstd). (Entered:\n03/26/2025)\n03/27/2025 44 RESPONSE by USA as to MALONE LAM re 43 Defendant's Proposed Scheduling Order (Attachments: # 1 Exhibit, # 2 Exhibit)\n(Rosenberg, Kevin) Modified to add link on 3/27/2025 (zstd). (Entered: 03/27/2025)\n03/28/2025 45 VACATED PURSUANT TO ORDER FILED 6/17/2025.....PRETRIAL SCHEDULING ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1). Signed by\nJudge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 3/28/2025. (lcckk3) Modified on 6/17/2025 (dot). (Entered: 03/28/2025)\n03/28/2025 46 MEMORANDUM OPINION re 45 Pretrial Scheduling Order as to MALONE LAM. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on\n3/28/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 03/28/2025)\n04/03/2025 47 MOTION for Extension of Time to Complete Discovery Production by USA as to MALONE LAM. (Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered:\n04/03/2025)\n04/03/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1): The Court is in receipt of the Government's 47 Motion for Extension of Time to Complete\nDiscovery. Therein, the Government requests a four-day extension of the discovery deadline in this matter (from April 7 to April 11). In\nsupport of its motion, the Government represents that a member of its support staff experienced a medical emergency and that the\nGovernment's discovery database experienced a \"fatal error\" that the Government is endeavoring to resolve. (Although the Court was\nunaware of the former issue, the Court has today received similar representations about technical problems with the Government's\ndiscovery system in other cases. See 25-cv-313.)\n\nDefendant Lam evidently opposes the Government's requested extension. Because the current discovery deadline is only two business\ndays from now, the Court ORDERS that Lam file a brief response to the Government's motion explaining the basis for his opposition by\n5:00 PM ET today, April 3, 2025. The Court will then resolve the matter promptly. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 4/3/2025.\n(lcckk3) (Entered: 04/03/2025)\n04/03/2025 48 RESPONSE regarding 47 Government's Proposed Extention of Time by MALONE LAM (Armstrong, Scott) Modified text and to add\nlink on 4/4/2025 (Entered: 04/03/2025)\n04/03/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1): For the reasons explained in the Court's earlier Minute Order, and because Defendant Lam\nnow represents that he does not oppose the Government's motion, see Notice, ECF No. 48 , the Court ORDERS that the Government's 47\nMotion for Extension of Time to Complete Discovery is GRANTED and that the Government shall complete its discovery productions on\nor before April 11, 2025. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 4/3/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 04/03/2025)\n04/03/2025 Set/Reset Deadlines as to MALONE LAM (1): Government's Discovery due by 4/11/2025. (dot) (Entered: 04/07/2025)\n04/29/2025 49 Consent MOTION to Continue May 12, 2025 Status Hearing by USA as to MALONE LAM. (Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered: 04/29/2025)\n04/30/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1): The Court is in receipt of the Government's 49 Consent Motion to Continue the status\nhearing currently scheduled for May 12, 2025. For the reasons stated therein, and with the parties' consent, the Court GRANTS the\nConsent Motion and CONTINUES the status hearing to 3:00 PM ET on MAY 19, 2025 in Courtroom 28A. Signed by Judge Colleen\nKollar-Kotelly on 4/30/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 04/30/2025)\n04/30/2025 Set/Reset Hearings as to MALONE LAM (1): Status Conference set for 5/19/2025 at 3:00 PM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge\nColleen Kollar-Kotelly. (dot) (Entered: 04/30/2025)\n04/30/2025 50 SUPERSEDING INDICTMENT as to MALONE LAM (1) count(s) 1s, 2s, 3s, MARLON FERRO (3) count(s) 1, 2, 3, HAMZA DOOST\n(4) count(s) 1, 3, CONOR FLANSBURG (5) count(s) 1, 2, KUNAL MEHTA (6) count(s) 1, 3, ETHAN YARALLY (7) count(s) 1, 2,\nCODY DEMIRTAS (8) count(s) 1, 2, AAKAASH ANAND (9) count(s) 1, 2, 3, EVAN TANGEMAN (10) count(s) 1, 3, JOEL CORTES\n(11) count(s) 1, 3, FNU LNU-1 (12) count(s) 1, 2, 3, FNU LNU-2 (13) count(s) 1, 2, 3, TUCKER DESMOND (14) count(s) 3, 4.\n(FORFEITURE) (zmcg). (Entered: 05/01/2025)\n04/30/2025 52 MOTION to Seal Case by USA as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON FERRO (3), HAMZA DOOST (4), CONOR FLANSBURG (5),\nKUNAL MEHTA (6), ETHAN YARALLY (7), CODY DEMIRTAS (8), AAKAASH ANAND (9), EVAN TANGEMAN (10), JOEL\nCORTES (11), FNU LNU-1 (12), FNU LNU-2 (13), TUCKER DESMOND (14). (Attachments: # 1 Text of Proposed Order)(zmcg)\n(Entered: 05/01/2025)\n04/30/2025 53 ORDER granting 52 Motion to Seal Case as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON FERRO (3), HAMZA DOOST (4), CONOR\nFLANSBURG (5), KUNAL MEHTA (6), ETHAN YARALLY (7), CODY DEMIRTAS (8), AAKAASH ANAND (9), EVAN\nTANGEMAN (10), JOEL CORTES (11), FNU LNU-1 (12), FNU LNU-2 (13), TUCKER DESMOND (14). Signed by Magistrate Judge\nMoxila A. Upadhyaya on 4/30/2025. (zmcg) (Entered: 05/02/2025)\n05/08/2025 54 AMENDED MOTION to Seal Case by USA as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON FERRO (3), HAMZA DOOST (4), CONOR\nFLANSBURG (5), KUNAL MEHTA (6), ETHAN YARALLY (7), CODY DEMIRTAS (8), AAKAASH ANAND (9), EVAN\nTANGEMAN (10), JOEL CORTES (11), FNU LNU-1 (12), FNU LNU-2 (13), TUCKER DESMOND (14). (Attachments: # 1 Text of\nProposed Order)(zstd) (Entered: 05/12/2025)\n05/12/2025 55 ORDER granting 54 Motion to Seal Case as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON FERRO (3), HAMZA DOOST (4), CONOR\nFLANSBURG (5), KUNAL MEHTA (6), ETHAN YARALLY (7), CODY DEMIRTAS (8), AAKAASH ANAND (9), EVAN\nTANGEMAN (10), JOEL CORTES (11), FNU LNU-1 (12), FNU LNU-2 (13), TUCKER DESMOND (14). Signed by Magistrate Judge\nMoxila A. Upadhyaya on 5/12/2025. (znjb) (Entered: 05/13/2025)\n05/13/2025 Arrest of KUNAL MEHTA in California. (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/13/2025 110 Arrest Warrant, dated 4/30/2025, Returned Executed on 5/13/2025 as to KUNAL MEHTA (6). (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/13/2025 Arrest of CONOR FLANSBURG in California. (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/13/2025 113 Arrest Warrant, dated 4/30/2025, Returned Executed on 5/13/2025 as to CONOR FLANSBURG (5). (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/13/2025 Arrest of JOEL CORTES in California. (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/13/2025 116 Arrest Warrant, dated 4/30/2025, Returned Executed on 5/13/2025 as to JOEL CORTES (11). (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/13/2025 Arrest of HAMZA DOOST in California. (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/13/2025 120 Arrest Warrant, dated 4/30/2025, Returned Executed on 5/13/2025 as to HAMZA DOOST (4). (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/13/2025 Arrest of MARLON FERRO in California. (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/13/2025 123 Arrest Warrant, dated 4/30/2025, Returned Executed on 5/13/2025 as to MARLON FERRO (3). (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/13/2025 Arrest of TUCKER DESMOND in California. (zmcg) (Entered: 05/30/2025)\n05/13/2025 129 Arrest Warrant, dated 4/30/2025, Returned Executed on 5/13/2025 as to TUCKER DESMOND (14). (zmcg) (Entered: 05/30/2025)\n05/13/2025 Arrest of EVAN TANGEMAN in California. (zmcg) (Entered: 05/30/2025)\n05/13/2025 132 Arrest Warrant, dated 4/30/2025, Returned Executed on 5/13/2025 as to EVAN TANGEMAN (10). (zmcg) (Entered: 05/30/2025)\n05/14/2025 61 MEMORANDUM OPINION AND ORDER as to HAMZA DOOST (4), KUNAL MEHTA (6). (This document is SEALED and only\navailable to authorized persons.) Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 5/14/25. (zdot) (Entered: 05/14/2025)\n05/14/2025 62 Emergency MOTION for De Novo Review of Magistrate's Release Order and Request to Stay Defendants's Release Pending De Novo\nReivew by USA as to HAMZA DOOST (4), KUNAL MEHTA (6). (zstd) (Entered: 05/15/2025)\n05/14/2025 63 Emergency MOTION for De Novo Review of Magistrate's Release Order and Request to Stay Defendant's Release Pending De Novo\nReview by USA as to HAMZA DOOST (4), KUNAL MEHTA (5). (Attachments: # 1 Text of Proposed Order)(zstd) (Entered: 05/15/2025)\n05/14/2025 64 SUPPLEMENT by USA as to HAMZA DOOST (4), KUNAL MEHTA (6) re 63 MOTION to Review and Stay (zstd) (Entered:\n05/15/2025)\n05/14/2025 65 SUPPLEMENT by USA as to HAMZA DOOST (4), KUNAL MEHTA (6) re 63 MOTION to Review and Stay (zstd) (Entered:\n05/15/2025)\n05/14/2025 66 MOTION to Unseal Case by USA as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON FERRO (3), HAMZA DOOST (4), CONOR FLANSBURG (5),\nKUNAL MEHTA (6), ETHAN YARALLY (7), CODY DEMIRTAS (8), AAKAASH ANAND (9), EVAN TANGEMAN (10), JOEL\nCORTES (11), FNU LNU-1 (12), FNU LNU-2 (13), TUCKER DESMOND (14). (zstd) (Entered: 05/15/2025)\n05/14/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON FERRO (3), HAMZA DOOST (4), CONOR FLANSBURG (5), KUNAL\nMEHTA (6), ETHAN YARALLY (7), CODY DEMIRTAS (8), AAKAASH ANAND (9), EVAN TANGEMAN (10), JOEL CORTES (11),\nFNU LNU-1 (12), FNU LNU-2 (13), TUCKER DESMOND (14): The Court is in receipt of the Government's 66 Motion to Unseal. For\nthe reasons stated therein, the Motion is GRANTED. (This document is SEALED and only available to authorized persons.) Signed by\nJudge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 5/14/25. (zdot) (Entered: 05/15/2025)\n05/15/2025 Case unsealed as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON FERRO (3), HAMZA DOOST (4), CONOR FLANSBURG (5), KUNAL MEHTA\n(6), ETHAN YARALLY (7), CODY DEMIRTAS (8), AAKAASH ANAND (9), EVAN TANGEMAN (10), JOEL CORTES (11), FNU\nLNU-1 (12), FNU LNU-2 (13), TUCKER DESMOND (14) (zstd) (Entered: 05/15/2025)\n05/15/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to HAMZA DOOST (4), KUNAL MEHTA (6): The Court is in receipt of the Government's 57 Emergency Motion\nfor De Novo Review and Request for Stay. The Court requires additional information before ruling on the Government's request for a stay.\nThe Government represents that Magistrate Judge McCormick has stayed his release order \"as the government prepares a fulsome filing\"\nfor this Court's review. The Government requests that this Court enter an additional stay \"while this filing is being finalized.\" But the\nGovernment's proposed order seeks a stay \"pending further notice from this Court.\"\n\nThe Court ORDERS that the Government promptly file a brief supplement clarifying: (1) The nature of the stay issued by Judge\nMcCormick (i.e. Has Judge McCormick stayed his order pending the Government filing its brief? pending resolution of the Government's\nappeal? pending transfer of the defendants to this District?); (2) The duration of the stay the Government requests from this Court; (3) The\nreason a stay from this Court is necessary given that Judge McCormick has already stayed his release order. If possible, the Government\nshould also identify the docket number of the case in C.D. Cal. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 5/14/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered:\n05/15/2025)\n05/15/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to HAMZA DOOST (4), KUNAL MEHTA (6): The Court is in receipt of the Government's 65 Supplement in\nresponse to the Court's earlier Minute Order. Therein, the Government clarifies that Judge McCormick's stay expires at 7:00 PM ET\ntonight, May 14, and that the Government is requesting that this Court issue a stay pending resolution of the Government's appeal. The\nCourt hereby ORDERS that by 5:00PM ET tonight, the Government shall file its motion for review of Judge McCormick's release order.\nBecause the Court cannot access the sealed docket in C.D. Cal., the Court further ORDERS that the Government shall attach copies of any\nfiled motions for detention or oppositions to those motions to the extent possible. When the Court is in receipt of these materials, the Court\nwill rule promptly on the Government's request for stay before the expiration of Judge McCormick's stay. The Court further ORDERS that\nthe Government shall inform defense counsel for Messrs. Doost and Mehta, so they may respond to the Government's motion for review.\nSigned by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 5/14/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 05/15/2025)\n05/15/2025 67 MOTION for De Novo Review of Magistrate's Release Order by USA as to MARLON FERRO (Rosenberg, Kevin) Modified event type\nand text on 5/16/2025 (zstd). (Entered: 05/15/2025)\n05/16/2025 68 MOTION to Set Status Hearing on the Superseding Indictment by USA as to MALONE LAM, JEANDIEL SERRANO, MARLON\nFERRO, HAMZA DOOST, CONOR FLANSBURG, KUNAL MEHTA, ETHAN YARALLY, CODY DEMIRTAS, AAKAASH ANAND,\nEVAN TANGEMAN, JOEL CORTES, FNU LNU-1, FNU LNU-2, TUCKER DESMOND. (Rosenberg, Kevin) Modified text on\n5/16/2025 (zstd). (Entered: 05/16/2025)\n05/16/2025 NOTICE OF HEARING as to MALONE LAM (1): Arraignment and Status Conference set for 5/19/2025 at 1:30 PM in Courtroom 28A-\nIn Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. (dot) (Entered: 05/16/2025)\n05/16/2025 NOTICE OF HEARING as to MARLON FERRO(3), CONOR FLANSBURG (5), EVAN TANGEMAN (10), JOEL CORTES (11),\nTUCKER DESMOND (14): Status Conference set for 5/19/2025 at 3:00 PM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-\nKotelly. (dot) (Entered: 05/16/2025)\n05/16/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON FERRO (3), HAMZA DOOST (4), CONOR FLANSBURG (5), KUNAL\nMEHTA (6), EVAN TANGEMAN (10), JOEL CORTES (11), and TUCKER DESMOND (14): The Court is in receipt of the\nGovernment's 68 Motion for Hearing, which states that Defendants Ferro (3), Doost (4), Flansburg (5), Mehta (6), Tangeman (10), Cortes\n(11), and Desmond (14) were arrested on the 50 Superseding Indictment in this case earlier this week and ordered by Magistrate Judge\nDouglas McCormick of the Central District of California to appear before this Court at 3:00 p.m. ET on May 19, 2025. The Court is\ninformed that counsel have been appointed or retained for each Defendant. Counsel shall promptly enter their appearances in this case.\n\nFor good cause shown, the Government's 68 Motion is GRANTED. It is ORDERED that Defendants Ferro (3), Flansburg (5), Tangeman\n(10), Cortes (11), and Desmond (14), their counsel, and Government counsel shall appear for a hearing at 3:00 p.m. ET on May 19, 2025,\nin Courtroom 28-A.\n\nIt is further ORDERED that the hearing for Defendant Lam (1) that was previously set for 3:00 p.m. ET on May 19 is RESCHEDULED to\n1:30 p.m. ET on the same day, May 19, 2025, in Courtroom 28-A.\nIt is further ORDERED that counsel for Defendants Doost (4) and Mehta (6) shall file any motions for reconsideration of this Court's 61\nOrder staying the pretrial release order entered by Magistrate Judge Douglas McCormick and/or responses to the Government's 62 Motion\nfor Review of Magistrate Judge McCormick's release order no later than 12:00 p.m. ET on May 20, 2025. The Government shall file any\nreply to these submissions no later than 5:00 p.m. ET on May 21, 2025.\n\nFinally, it is ORDERED that counsel for Defendant Ferro (3) shall file a response to the Government's 67 Motion for Review of\nMagistrate Judge McCormick's pretrial release order no later than 12:00 p.m. ET on May 20, 2025. The Government shall file any reply to\nthis submission no later than 5:00 p.m. ET on May 21, 2025.\n\nThe Court shall set a hearing for Defendants Doost (4) and Mehta (6) by further order. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on\n05/16/2025. (lcckk1) (Entered: 05/16/2025)\n\n05/17/2025 69 MOTION to Vacate Trial Date and Pre-Trial Scheduling Order by USA as to MALONE LAM. (Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered: 05/17/2025)\n05/17/2025 70 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Alvin H. Thomas, Jr appearing for TUCKER DESMOND (Thomas, Alvin) (Entered:\n05/17/2025)\n05/18/2025 71 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Nick Oberheiden appearing for CONOR FLANSBURG (Oberheiden, Nick) (Entered:\n05/18/2025)\n05/18/2025 72 MOTION for Leave to Appear Pro Hac Vice Shrey Sharma Filing fee $ 100, receipt number ADCDC-11697662. Fee Status: Fee Paid. by\nCONOR FLANSBURG. (Attachments: # 1 Declaration of Shrey Sharma, # 2 Certificate of Good Standing)(Oberheiden, Nick) (Entered:\n05/18/2025)\n05/19/2025 73 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Dwight E. Crawley appearing for EVAN TANGEMAN (Crawley, Dwight) (Entered:\n05/19/2025)\n05/19/2025 74 ORDER as to MARLON FERRO (3), HAMZA DOOST (4), CONOR FLANSBURG (5), KUNAL MEHTA (6), EVAN TANGEMAN\n(10), JOEL CORTES (11), and TUCKER DESMOND (14) confirming the Government's disclosure obligations under Brady v. Maryland.\nSigned by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 05/19/2025. (lcckk1) (Entered: 05/19/2025)\n05/19/2025 75 ENTERED IN ERROR.....NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Kevin Eugene Wilson appearing for MARLON FERRO (Wilson,\nKevin) Modified on 5/20/2025 (zstd). (Entered: 05/19/2025)\n05/19/2025 MINUTE ORDER granting 72 Motion for Leave to Appear Pro Hac Vice Counsel should register for e-filing via PACER and file a\nnotice of appearance pursuant to LCrR 44.5(a). Click for instructions Attorney Shrey Sharma as to CONOR FLANSBURG (5). Signed\nby Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 5/19/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 05/19/2025)\n05/19/2025 76 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Barry Coburn appearing for HAMZA DOOST (Coburn, Barry) (Entered: 05/19/2025)\n05/19/2025 77 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: George Allen Dale appearing for JOEL CORTES (Dale, George) (Entered: 05/19/2025)\n05/19/2025 83 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Shrey Sharma appearing for CONOR FLANSBURG (Sharma, Shrey) (Entered: 05/19/2025)\n05/19/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1): The Court held a status hearing in this matter on May 19, 2025. Defendant, his counsel, the\nGovernment, and a court reporter were present in person.\n\nThe Court began by arraigning Defendant Lam on the 50 Superseding Indictment. Defendant waived formal reading of the superseding\nindictment and pleaded not guilty to all charges. The Government reported that it would begin producing new discovery relating to the\nsuperseding indictment next week.\n\nNext, as discussed at the last status hearing in this matter, Min. Order (Mar. 7, 2025), the Court reviewed on the record the Government's\nmost recent plea offer. Defendant confirmed that he had reviewed the offer with his counsel, understood the terms of the offer, and rejected\nthe offer.\n\nNext, the Court discussed with the parties the Government's pending 69 Motion to Vacate the trial date and pretrial scheduling order.\nDefendant represented that he may oppose the motion, but requested time to discuss the matter with counsel for the new co-defendants\nadded via superseding indictment. Defendant further represented that he may file a motion to sever. To avoid any wasteful duplication of\neffort by the Court and parties while Defendant evaluates how he intends to proceed, the Court ORDERS that all deadlines governed by\nthe 45 Pretrial Scheduling Order are held in abeyance and tolled pending resolution of the Government's Motion to Vacate and any\nforthcoming motion to sever. When such motions are resolved, the Court will amend or vacate the Pretrial Scheduling Order as necessary.\n\nNext, the Government brought to the Court's attention a potential conflict of interest involving defense counsel for Defendant Lam and a\nnewly-added co-defendant. As discussed, the Court ORDERS that the Government and defense counsel file a joint motion regarding this\nissue on or before JUNE 2, 2025. The Court further ORDERS that the parties appear for a status hearing and a hearing on the forthcoming\njoint motion regarding conflicts at 1:30 PM ET on JUNE 20, 2025 in Courtroom 28A.\n\nFinally, the Court discussed with Defendant Lam his Speedy Trial Act rights. Defendant asserted his right to a speedy trial and did not\nconsent to tolling. In light of the additional complexity in this case occasioned by the superseding indictment, the need for defense counsel\nto review additional discovery and coordinate with counsel for co-defendants, and the pending and forthcoming motions regarding\nvacatur, severance, and conflicts, the Court finds that the ends of justice served by excluding Speedy Trial time on the original indictment\noutweigh the interests of Defendant and the public in a speedy trial. 18 USC 3161(h)(7)(A). Accordingly, the Court will exclude the time\nbetween May 12, 2025 (the date this hearing was originally scheduled) and June 20, 2025, from the speedy trial clock on the original\nindictment. As to the superseding indictment, Defendant's speedy trial time is tolled to June 20, 2025 in parallel with his co-defendants. 18\nUSC 3161(h)(6). Taking into account these exclusions, the Court calculates that Defendant's 70-day deadline is August 29, 2025 and that\nhis 90-day deadline is September 18, 2025. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 5/19/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 05/19/2025)\n05/19/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly: Arraignment as to MALONE LAM (1) on Counts 1s,2s,3s held\non 5/19/2025. Plea of Not Guilty entered as to All Counts. Defendant objected to the tolling of his Speedy Trial Rights; the Court shall\nmake a ruling. Status Conference as to MALONE LAM held on 5/19/2025. Status Conference set for 6/20/2025 at 1:30 PM in Courtroom\n28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Conflict Hearing set for 6/20/2025 at 2:30 PM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before\nJudge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Bond Status of Defendant: COMMITTED/COMMITMENT ISSUED; Court Reporter: Chandra Kean;\nDefense Attorney: Patrick Queenan and Scott Armstrong; US Attorney: Kevin L. Rosenberg. (dot) (Entered: 05/19/2025)\n05/19/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MARLON FERRO (3), CONOR FLANSBURG (5), EVAN TANGEMAN (10), JOEL CORTES (11), and\nTUCKER DESMOND (14): The Court held a status hearing in this matter on May 19, 2025. Defendants Ferro, Flansburg, Tangeman,\nCortes, and Desmond; their counsel; the Government; a court reporter; and a representative from Pretrial Services were present in person.\n\nThe Court began by arraigning the Defendants on the 50 Superseding Indictment. Defendants Ferro, Flansburg, Tangeman, Cortes, and\nDesmond each waived formal reading of the superseding indictment and pleaded not guilty to all charges. The Government reported that it\nwould promptly begin producing to Defendants all discovery already produced to Defendant Lam. The Government further reported that it\nwill begin producing new discovery on the superseding indictment shortly and will coordinate with defense counsel on the logistics for\nproviding hard drives to facilitate discovery production. The Court also discussed with defense counsel the possibility of participating in\nthe discovery coordination program. Eligible Defendants may file a joint motion to participate in that program if they so choose.\nNext, the Government requested that the 24 Protective Order in this matter be extended to these new Defendants. The Court distributed\ncopies of the Protective Order to defense counsel, none of whom objected at the hearing. The Court ORDERS that the Government\npromptly file a motion formally requesting that a protective order be imposed as to these Defendants. The Court will resolve that motion,\nand any objections thereto, in due course.\n\nPretrial Services reviewed the conditions of release with the Defendants. Defendants Cortes and Desmond each requested that their\nconditions of release be modified to allow for the use of additional email accounts and for the return of their cell phones. Defendants\nCortes and Desmond will coordinate with the Government on these issues and file a motion as necessary.\n\nThe Court ORDERS that the parties appear for a further status hearing in this matter at 11:30 AM ET on JUNE 20, 2025. Defense\ncounsel shall appear in person. Defendants may appear via Zoom videoconference.\n\nFinally, the Court discussed with Defendants their Speedy Trial Act rights. In light of the unusual complexity of this matter occasioned by\nthe number of co-defendants, the breadth of the charged conspiracy, and the volume of discovery (including substantial phone and\ncomputer extractions); and with the consent of all present Defendants; the Court finds that the ends of justice served by excluding Speedy\nTrial time until the next status hearing outweigh the interests of Defendants and the public in a speedy trial and that it would be\nunreasonable to expect adequate preparation for proceedings in this matter under the time limits ordinarily prescribed by the Speedy Trial\nAct. 18 USC 3161(h)(7)(A), (B)(ii). Accordingly, the Court will exclude the time between May 19, 2025 (the date of Defendants' initial\nappearance in this District) and June 20, 2025, from the speedy trial clock. Taking into account this exclusion, the Court calculates that\neach Defendant's 70-day deadline is August 29, 2025. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 5/19/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered:\n05/19/2025)\n05/19/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly: Arraignment as to MARLON FERRO (3) on Counts 1,2,3 and\nCONOR FLANSBURG (5) on Counts 1,2 and EVAN TANGEMAN (10) on Counts 1,3 and JOEL CORTES (11) on Counts 1,3 and\nTUCKER DESMOND (14) on Counts 3,4 held on 5/19/2025. Plea of Not Guilty on All Counts as to All Defendants. Status Conference as\nto MARLON FERRO, CONOR FLANSBURG, EVAN TANGEMAN, JOEL CORTES, TUCKER DESMOND held on 5/19/2025.\nExcludable started as to MARLON FERRO, CONOR FLANSBURG, EVAN TANGEMAN, JOEL CORTES, TUCKER DESMOND.\nSpeedy Trial (XT) is tolled as to All Defendants from 5/19/2025 to 6/20/2025.Status Conference as to All Defendants set for 6/20/2025 at\n11:30 AM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Defense counsel shall appear in person. Defendants may\nappear via Zoom videoconference.Bond Status of Defendants: Personal Recognizance as to All Defendants; Court Reporter: Chandra\nKean; Defense Attorney: (3)-Kevin Wilson, (5)-Shrey Sharma, (10)-Dwight Crawley, (11)-Alan Dales, (14)-Alvin Thomas; US Attorney:\nKevin L. Rosenberg; Pretrial Officer: Britney Dahlkoetter. (dot) (Entered: 05/20/2025)\n05/19/2025 89 ORDER Setting Conditions of Release as to MARLON FERRO (3) Personal Recognizance. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on\n5/19/20. (Attachments: # 1 APPEARANCE BOND) (dot) (Entered: 05/20/2025)\n05/19/2025 90 ORDER Setting Conditions of Release as to CONOR FLANSBURG (5) Personal Recognizance. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly\non 5/19/25. (Attachments: # 1 APPEARANCE BOND) (dot) (Entered: 05/20/2025)\n05/19/2025 91 ORDER Setting Conditions of Release as to EVAN TANGEMAN (10) Personal Recognizance. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly\non 5/19/25. (Attachments: # 1 APPEARANCE BOND) (dot) (Entered: 05/20/2025)\n05/19/2025 92 ORDER Setting Conditions of Release as to JOEL CORTES (11) Personal Recognizance. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on\n5/19/25. (Attachments: # 1 APPEARANCE BOND) (dot) (Entered: 05/20/2025)\n05/19/2025 93 ORDER Setting Conditions of Release as to TUCKER DESMOND (14) Personal Recognizance. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly\non 5/19/25. (Attachments: # 1 APPEARANCE BOND) (dot) (Entered: 05/20/2025)\n05/20/2025 NOTICE OF ERROR as to MARLON FERRO regarding 75 Notice of Attorney Appearance - Defendant. The following error(s) need\ncorrection: The Notice of Appearance needs to be signed by the attorney Other- Please refile signed NOA in PDF format. (zstd) (Entered:\n05/20/2025)\n05/20/2025 84 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Kevin Eugene Wilson appearing for MARLON FERRO (Wilson, Kevin) (Entered:\n05/20/2025)\n05/20/2025 85 MOTION for Reconsideration re 61 Sealed Order Relating to Conditions of Release by HAMZA DOOST. (Attachments: # 1 Text of\nProposed Order)(Coburn, Barry) (Entered: 05/20/2025)\n05/20/2025 86 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Addy R. Schmitt appearing for KUNAL MEHTA (Schmitt, Addy) (Entered: 05/20/2025)\n05/20/2025 87 MOTION for Leave to Appear Pro Hac Vice Alan Eisner Filing fee $ 100, receipt number ADCDC-11702178. Fee Status: Fee Paid. by\nKUNAL MEHTA. (Attachments: # 1 Declaration of Alan Eisner, # 2 Exhibit Certificate of Standing)(Schmitt, Addy) (Entered:\n05/20/2025)\n05/20/2025 88 MOTION for Reconsideration re Order on Motion for Hearing,,,,,,,, by KUNAL MEHTA. (Attachments: # 1 Declaration of Alan Eisner, #\n2 Exhibit to Eisner Declaration)(Schmitt, Addy) (Entered: 05/20/2025)\n05/20/2025 ORDER granting 87 Motion for Leave to Appear Pro Hac Vice Counsel should register for e-filing via PACER and file a notice of\nappearance pursuant to LCrR 44.5(a). Click for instructions Attorney Alan Eisner as to KUNAL MEHTA (6). Signed by Judge Colleen\nKollar-Kotelly on 5/20/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 05/20/2025)\n05/21/2025 94 REPLY TO OPPOSITION to Motion by USA as to KUNAL MEHTA re 88 MOTION for Reconsideration re Order on Motion for\nHearing,,,,,,,, (Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered: 05/21/2025)\n05/21/2025 95 REPLY TO OPPOSITION to Motion by USA as to HAMZA DOOST re 85 MOTION for Reconsideration re 61 Sealed Order Relating to\nConditions of Release (Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered: 05/21/2025)\n05/21/2025 96 MOTION for Leave to File Response to Government's Motion for de novo review of Magistrate's release order out of time by MARLON\nFERRO. (Wilson, Kevin) (Entered: 05/21/2025)\n05/21/2025 97 RESPONSE by MARLON FERRO re 67 MOTION to Review (Attachments: # 1 Exhibit A, # 2 Exhibit B)(Wilson, Kevin) (Entered:\n05/21/2025)\n05/21/2025 MINUTE ORDER granting 96 Motion for Leave to File out of time as to MARLON FERRO (3). Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly\non 5/21/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 05/21/2025)\n05/21/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to KUNAL MEHTA (6): The Government has represented that Defendant Mehta \"assisted [Coconspirators] with\nobtaining firearms to protect themselves against rival cybercrime groups.\" To facilitate the Court's resolution of the pending 67 88 motions\nrelated to Mehta's detention, the Court ORDERS that the Government file a brief supplement further explaining that representation by\n9:00 AM ET, tomorrow May 22, 2025. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 5/21/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 05/21/2025)\n05/21/2025 98 REPLY by USA as to MARLON FERRO re 67 MOTION for Review (Rosenberg, Kevin) Modified text and to add correct link 5/23/2025\n(zstd). (Entered: 05/21/2025)\n05/21/2025 99 RESPONSE TO ORDER OF THE COURT by USA as to KUNAL MEHTA re Order,, (Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered: 05/21/2025)\n05/22/2025 100 ORDER as to HAMZA DOOST (4) and KUNAL MEHTA (6) directing further submissions to inform the Court's consideration of the\npending motions regarding pretrial detention. The stay of the release orders entered by Magistrate Judge Douglas McCormick remains in\neffect until further order of this Court. See Order for further details. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 05/22/2025. (lcckk1)\n(Entered: 05/22/2025)\n05/22/2025 101 ORDER as to MARLON FERRO (3) directing further submissions to inform the Court's consideration of the pending motions regarding\npretrial detention. See Order for further details. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 05/22/2025. (lcckk1) (Entered: 05/22/2025)\n05/22/2025 102 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Eugene V. Gorokhov appearing for TUCKER DESMOND (Gorokhov, Eugene) (Entered:\n05/22/2025)\n05/23/2025 105 MOTION to Withdraw as Attorney by Scott Armstrong and Patrick Queenan. by MALONE LAM. (Attachments: # 1 Text of Proposed\nOrder, # 2 Exhibit, # 3 Exhibit)(Armstrong, Scott) (Entered: 05/23/2025)\n05/23/2025 106 Consent MOTION to Modify Conditions of Release by JOEL CORTES. (Dale, George) (Entered: 05/23/2025)\n05/28/2025 108 Consent MOTION for Protective Order Governing Discovery by USA as to MALONE LAM, MARLON FERRO, HAMZA DOOST,\nCONOR FLANSBURG, KUNAL MEHTA, EVAN TANGEMAN, JOEL CORTES and TUCKER DESMOND. (Rosenberg, Kevin)\nModified to remove incorrect linked defendants on 5/30/2025 (zstd). (Entered: 05/28/2025)\n05/29/2025 109 Protective Order as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON FERRO (3), HAMZA DOOST (4), CONOR FLANSBURG (5), KUNAL MEHTA\n(6), EVAN TANGEMAN (10), JOEL CORTES (11), TUCKER DESMOND (14). Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 5/29/2025.\n(lcckk3) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/29/2025 111 Rule 5(c)(3) Documents Received as to KUNAL MEHTA (6) from United States District Court for the Central District of California\n(Southern Division - Santa Ana) Case Number 8:25-mj-00388 (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/29/2025 114 Rule 5(c)(3) Documents Received as to CONOR FLANSBURG (5) from United States District Court for the Central District of California\n(Southern Division - Santa Ana) Case Number 8:25-mj-00386 (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/29/2025 117 Rule 5(c)(3) Documents Received as to JOEL CORTES (11) from United States District Court for the Central District of California\n(Southern Division - Santa Ana) Case Number 8:25-mj-00391 (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/29/2025 119 MOTION for Leave to Appear Pro Hac Vice Dmitry Gorin Filing fee $ 100, receipt number ADCDC-11722296. Fee Status: Fee Paid. by\nKUNAL MEHTA. (Attachments: # 1 Declaration of Dmitry Gorin, # 2 Exhibit Certificate of Standing)(Schmitt, Addy) (Entered:\n05/29/2025)\n05/29/2025 121 Rule 5(c)(3) Documents Received as to HAMZA DOOST (4) from United States District Court for the Central District of California\n(Southern Division - Santa Ana) Case Number 8:25-mj-00389 (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/29/2025 124 Rule 5(c)(3) Documents Received as to MARLON FERRO (3) from United States District Court for the Central District of California\n(Southern Division - Santa Ana) Case Number 8:25-mj-00387 (zmcg) (Entered: 05/29/2025)\n05/30/2025 130 Rule 5(c)(3) Documents Received as to TUCKER DESMOND (14) from United States District Court for the Central District of California\n(Southern Division - Santa Ana) Case Number 8:25-mj-00395 (zmcg) (Entered: 05/30/2025)\n05/30/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to JOEL CORTES (11): The Court is in receipt of Defendant Cortes's 106 Motion to Modify Release Conditions.\nThe Court ORDERS that Cortes, his counsel, and the Government appear for a hearing on the motion at 3:00 PM ET on JUNE 4, 2025\nvia Zoom. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 5/30/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 05/30/2025)\n05/30/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to KUNAL MEHTA (6) granting 119 Motion for Leave to Appear Pro Hac Vice. Attorney Dmitry Gorin as counsel\nfor Defendant Kunal Mehta. Counsel should register for e-filing via PACER and file a notice of appearance pursuant to LCrR\n44.5(a). Click for instructions. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 5/30/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 05/30/2025)\n05/30/2025 133 Rule 5(c)(3) Documents Received as to EVAN TANGEMAN (10) from United States District Court for the Central District of California\n(Southern Division - Santa Ana) Case Number 8:25-mj-00396 (zmcg) (Entered: 05/30/2025)\n05/30/2025 Set/Reset Hearings as to JOEL CORTES (11): Motion Hearing set for 6/4/2025 at 3:00 PM via videoconference before Judge Colleen\nKollar-Kotelly. (zakb) (Entered: 05/30/2025)\n05/30/2025 135 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: John Patrick Pierce appearing for MALONE LAM (Pierce, John) (Entered: 05/30/2025)\n05/30/2025 136 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Alan Eisner appearing for KUNAL MEHTA (Eisner, Alan) (Entered: 05/30/2025)\n06/02/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1): The Court ORDERS that Defendant Lam, his counsel, and the Government appear for a\nhearing on the 105 Motion to Withdraw at 9:00 AM ET on JUNE 4, 2025 in Courtroom 28A. Attorney Queenan will appear via Zoom.\nSigned by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 6/2/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 06/02/2025)\n06/02/2025 137 MEMORANDUM OPINION & ORDER granting 62 63 Motions for Review as to KUNAL MEHTA (6); denying 88 Motion for\nReconsideration as to KUNAL MEHTA (6); and ordering that KUNAL MEHTA (6) be detained pending trial. Signed by Judge Colleen\nKollar-Kotelly on 6/2/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 06/02/2025)\n06/02/2025 138 ORDER granting in part and denying in part 62 63 Motions for Review as to HAMZA DOOST (4); granting in part and denying in part 85\nMotion for Reconsideration as to HAMZA DOOST (4); and ordering that HAMZA DOOST (4) be released pending trial subject to\nadditional conditions. This Court's stay of release shall lift automatically upon the satisfaction of the terms described herein. Signed by\nJudge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 6/2/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 06/02/2025)\n06/02/2025 139 MEMORANDUM OPINION as to HAMZA DOOST accompanying 138 Order. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 6/2/2025.\n(Attachments: # 1 Appendix A Original Release Conditions) (lcckk3) (Entered: 06/02/2025)\n06/02/2025 Set/Reset Hearings as to MALONE LAM (1): Status Conference set for 6/4/2025 at 9:00 AM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge\nColleen Kollar-Kotelly. (dot) (Entered: 06/04/2025)\n06/03/2025 140 MEMORANDUM OPINION & ORDER as to MARLON FERRO (3) granting in part and denying in part the Government's 67 Motion\nfor Review. The Government's request for de novo review is GRANTED, the Government's request that Defendant Ferro be detained\npending trial is DENIED, and Defendant Ferro's conditions of release are MODIFIED as described herein. Signed by Judge Colleen\nKollar-Kotelly on 06/03/2025. (lcckk1) (Entered: 06/03/2025)\n06/04/2025 142 AMENDED ORDER Setting Conditions of Release as to MARLON FERRO (3) Personal Recognizance. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-\nKotelly on 6/3/25. (dot) (Entered: 06/04/2025)\n06/04/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1): The Court held a hearing in this matter on June 4, 2025. Defendant Lam; defense counsel\nMessrs. Armstrong, Queenan, and Pierce; the Government; and a court reporter were present.\n\nThe Court began by discussing Attorneys Armstrong and Queenan's 105 Motion to Withdraw. Defendant Lam consented to the Motion.\nAccordingly, for the reasons stated in the motion and on the record, the Court orally GRANTED the Motion to Withdraw. Scott Armstrong\nand Patrick Queenan withdrawn from case.\nNext, the Court discussed with Defendant Lam and Attorney Pierce the Government's pending 69 Motion to Vacate the trial date and\npretrial scheduling order. Defendant Lam reiterated his opposition to the motion. Accordingly, the Court ORDERS that Defendant Lam\nfile a Motion to Sever on or before June 11, 2025. The Government shall file its opposition on or before June 16, 2025.\n\nFinally, in light of Attorneys Armstrong and Queenan's withdrawal, the Court VACATES the conflicts hearing scheduled for 1:30 PM on\nJune 20, 2025 and ORDERS that Defendant Lam appear for the status hearing scheduled for 11:30 AM ET on JUNE 20, 2025 in\nCourtroom 28A. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 6/4/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 06/04/2025)\n06/04/2025 143 ORDER granting 106 Motion to Modify Conditions of Release as to JOEL CORTES (11). Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on\n6/4/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 06/04/2025)\n06/04/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly: Status Conference as to MALONE LAM (1) held on 6/4/2025.\nThe Court granted 105 Motion to Withdraw Attorneys Scott Armstrong and Patrick Queenan as to MALONE LAM. Defendant's Motion\nto Sever due by 6/11/2025. Government's Response due by 6/16/2025. The Court vacated the Conflict Hearing set for 6/20/2025. Status\nConference set for 6/20/2025 at 11:30 AM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Bond Status of Defendant:\nCOMMITTED/COMMITMENT ISSUED; Court Reporter: Lisa Moreira; Defense Attorney: John P. Pierce, Scott Armstrong and Patrick\nQueenan; US Attorney: Kevin L. Rosenberg. (dot) (Entered: 06/05/2025)\n06/04/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly: Status Conference as to JOEL CORTES (11) held on 6/4/2025.\nThe Court granted 106 Motion to Modify Conditions of Release. Status Conference set for 6/20/2025 at 11:30 AM in Courtroom 28A- In\nPerson before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Bond Status of Defendant: Personal Recognizance; Court Reporter: Chandra Kean; Defense\nAttorney: George A. Dale; US Attorney: Kevin L. Rosenberg; Pretrial Officer: Shania Fennell. (dot) (Entered: 06/05/2025)\n06/05/2025 144 MOTION for Reconsideration re 137 Order on Motion for Review,, Order on Motion to Stay,,,,,, Order on Motion for Reconsideration,\nMotion to Re-Open Detention Hearing by KUNAL MEHTA. (Attachments: # 1 Exhibit A - Declaration of Karan Mehta, # 2 Exhibit B -\nDeclaration of Lynn Hendricks)(Eisner, Alan) (Entered: 06/05/2025)\n06/05/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to KUNAL MEHTA (6): The Government shall respond to the 144 Motion for Reconsideration by 12:00 PM on\nJUNE 11, 2025. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 6/5/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 06/05/2025)\n06/05/2025 145 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Dmitry Gorin appearing for KUNAL MEHTA (Gorin, Dmitry) (Entered: 06/05/2025)\n06/05/2025 Set/Reset Deadlines as to KUNAL MEHTA: Government's Response to 144 due by 6/11/2025. (dot) (Entered: 06/09/2025)\n06/11/2025 146 SUPPLEMENTAL REPLY by USA as to KUNAL MEHTA re 144 MOTION for Reconsideration re 137 Order on Motion for Review,,\nOrder on Motion to Stay,,,,,, Order on Motion for Reconsideration, Motion to Re-Open Detention Hearing (Attachments: # 1 Exhibit Ex.\n1)(Rosenberg, Kevin) Modified text on 6/12/2025 (zstd). (Entered: 06/11/2025)\n06/12/2025 154 NOTICE of Additional Rule 5 Documents by HAMZA DOOST (4) re 121 Rule 5 Documents Received (zmcg) (Entered: 06/18/2025)\n06/16/2025 155 NOTICE of Additional Rule 5 Documents by TUCKER DESMOND (14) re 130 Rule 5 Documents Received (zmcg) (Entered:\n06/18/2025)\n06/17/2025 150 ORDER denying 148 Sealed Motion (This document is SEALED and only available to authorized persons.) as to MALONE LAM (1);\ngranting 69 Motion to Vacate as to MALONE LAM (1). Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 6/17/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered:\n06/17/2025)\n06/17/2025 151 MOTION to Modify Conditions of Release by TUCKER DESMOND. (Gorokhov, Eugene) (Entered: 06/17/2025)\n06/17/2025 ORAL MOTION for Speedy Trial by USA as to KUNAL MEHTA (6). (znjb) (Entered: 06/17/2025)\n06/17/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Moxila A. Upadhyaya: First Appearance in the District/Arraignment as to\nKUNAL MEHTA (6) held on 6/17/2025. Defendant present in the courtroom. Not Guilty Plea entered as to Counts 1,3. The Court advised\nthe Government of its Due Process Obligations under Rule 5(f). Defendant has Retained Counsel. Oral Motion by the Government for\nSpeedy Trial as to KUNAL MEHTA (6); heard and granted. Speedy Trial Excluded between 6/17/2025 to 6/20/2025 in the Interest of\nJustice (XT). Status Conference set for 6/20/2025 at 11:30 AM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Bond\nStatus of Defendant: Defendant Committed/Commitment Issued; Court Reporter: FTR- GOLD; FTR Time Frame: CRTM 5: [12:43:53-\n12:54:03]; Defense Attorney: Addy Schmitt; US Attorney: Diane Lucas for Kevin Rosenberg; Pretrial Officer: Da'Shanta Lewis. (znjb)\n(Entered: 06/17/2025)\n06/17/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to KUNAL MEHTA (6): As required by Rule 5(f), the United States is ordered to produce all exculpatory evidence\nto the defendant pursuant to Brady v. Maryland and its progeny. Not doing so in a timely manner may result in sanctions, including\nexclusion of evidence, adverse jury instructions, dismissal of charges and contempt proceedings. Signed by Magistrate Judge Moxila A.\nUpadhyaya on 6/17/2025. (znjb) (Entered: 06/17/2025)\n06/18/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to HAMZA DOOST (4): The Court ORDERS that Defendant Doost shall appear via Zoom appear for the status\nhearing scheduled for 11:30 AM ET on JUNE 20, 2025. Counsel for Defendant Doost shall appear in person. Signed by Judge Colleen\nKollar-Kotelly on 6/18/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 06/18/2025)\n06/20/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON FERRO (3), CONOR FLANSBURG (5), KUNAL MEHTA (6), EVAN\nTANGEMAN (10): The Court held a status hearing in this matter on June 20, 2025. Defendants Lam and Mehta were present in person.\nDefendants Ferro, Flansburg, and Tangeman were present via Zoom with their consent. Counsel for all defendants were present in person.\n\nThe Court began by discussing the status of discovery productions. The Government reported that Defendants Lam, Flansburg, and\nTangeman have all received the initial tranche of discovery. The Government is working with counsel for Defendants Ferro and Mehta to\narrange for this initial production. The Government further reported that additional discovery productions will be made on a rolling basis.\nIn response to questions from counsel for Defendants Lam and Mehta, the Court will inquire about procedures for viewing discovery at\ntheir detention facilities. The Court also understands that counsel for some defendants are pursuing the appointment of a Coordinating\nDiscovery Attorney.\n\nThe Government reported that plea discussions are ongoing. Given the volume of discovery, counsel for some defendants requested\nadditional time to review discovery. Accordingly, the Court ORDERS that Defendants Lam, Ferro, Flansburg, Mehta, and Tangeman shall\nappear for a status hearing at 1:30 PM ET on AUGUST 28, 2025. Defendants Ferro, Flansburg, and Tangeman shall appear via Zoom.\nDefendants Lam and Mehta and counsel for all defendants shall appear in person.\n\nNext, the Court discussed with Defendants their Speedy Trial Act rights. Defendant Lam asserted his right to a speedy trial. Defendants\nFerro, Flansburg, Mehta, and Tangeman each consented to the exclusion of time until the next status hearing. In light of the unusual\ncomplexity of this matter occasioned by the number of co-defendants, the breadth of the charged conspiracy, and the volume of discovery\n(including substantial phone and computer extractions); the Court finds that the ends of justice served by excluding Speedy Trial time until\nthe next status hearing outweigh the interests of Defendants and the public in a speedy trial and that it would be unreasonable to expect\nadequate preparation for proceedings in this matter under the time limits ordinarily prescribed by the Speedy Trial Act. 18 USC 3161(h)(7)\n(A), (B)(ii). Accordingly, the Court will exclude the time between June 20, 2025 and August 28, 2025, from the speedy trial clock. Taking\ninto account this exclusion, the Court calculates that each Defendant's 70-day deadline is November 7, 2025; Defendant Lam's and\nDefendant Mehta's 90-day deadlines are November 27, 2025.\n\nFinally, the Court discussed Defendant Mehta's pending 144 Motion for Reconsideration. The Court ORDERS that Defendant Mehta, his\ncounsel, and the Government appear for a hearing on that motion at 2:30 PM ET on JUNE 23, 2025 in Courtroom 28A. The Court\nORDERS that Defendant Mehta's brother appear via Zoom for examination by the Court and Government regarding his suitability as a\npotential third-party custodian. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 6/20/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 06/20/2025)\n06/20/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to HAMZA DOOST (4), JOEL CORTES (11), TUCKER DESMOND (14): The Court held a status hearing in this\nmatter on June 20, 2025. Defendants Doost, Cortes, and Desmond were present via Zoom with their consent. Counsel for all defendants\nwere present in person.\n\nThe Court began by discussing the status of discovery productions. The Government reported that each Defendant has received the initial\ntranche of discovery. The Government further reported that additional discovery productions will be made on a rolling basis. The Court\nalso understands that counsel for some defendants are pursuing the appointment of a Coordinating Discovery Attorney.\n\nThe Government reported that plea discussions are ongoing. Given the volume of discovery, counsel for some defendants requested\nadditional time to review discovery. Accordingly, the Court ORDERS that Defendants Doost, Cortes, and Desmond shall appear for a\nstatus hearing at 2:30 PM ET on AUGUST 28, 2025 via Zoom. Defense counsel shall appear in person in Courtroom 28A.\n\nNext, the Court discussed with Defendants their Speedy Trial Act rights. Defendants Doost, Cortes, and Desmond each consented to the\nexclusion of time until the next hearing. In light of the unusual complexity of this matter occasioned by the number of co-defendants, the\nbreadth of the charged conspiracy, and the volume of discovery (including substantial phone and computer extractions); the Court finds\nthat the ends of justice served by excluding Speedy Trial time until the next status hearing outweigh the interests of Defendants and the\npublic in a speedy trial and that it would be unreasonable to expect adequate preparation for proceedings in this matter under the time\nlimits ordinarily prescribed by the Speedy Trial Act. 18 USC 3161(h)(7)(A), (B)(ii). Accordingly, the Court will exclude the time between\nJune 20, 2025 and August 28, 2025, from the speedy trial clock. Taking into account this exclusion, the Court calculates that each\nDefendant's 70-day deadline is November 7, 2025.\n\nFinally, the Court discussed Defendant Desmond's pending 151 Motion to Modify Conditions of Release. The Court ORDERS that the\nGovernment respond to this motion on or before JUNE 23, 2025. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 6/20/2025. (lcckk3)\n(Entered: 06/20/2025)\n06/20/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly: Status Conference as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON\nFERRO(3), HAMZA DOOST (4), CONOR FLANSBURG (5), KUNAL MEHTA (6), EVAN TANGEMAN (10), JOEL CORTES (11),\nTUCKER DESMOND (14) held on 6/20/2025. Excludable started as to MARLON FERRO, HAMZA DOOST, CONOR FLANSBURG,\nKUNAL MEHTA, EVAN TANGEMAN, JOEL CORTES, TUCKER DESMOND. Speedy Trial (XT) is tolled in the Interest of Justice for\nDefendants FERRO, DOOST, FLANSBURG, MEHTA, TANGEMAN, CORTES, DESMOND, from 6/20/2025 to 8/28/2025. Defendant\nLAM asserted his right to a speedy trial. Status Conference as to LAM, MEHTA, FERRO, TANGMAN, FLANSBURG set for 8/28/2025\nat 1:30 PM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Status Conference as to DOOST, CORTES, DESMOND\nset for 8/28/2025 at 2:30 PM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Bond Status of Defendant:\nCOMMITTED/COMMITMENT ISSUED as to KUNAL MEHTA and MALONE LAM and PERSONAL RECOGNIZANCE as to\nMALON FERRO, CONOR FLANSBURG, EVAN TANGEMAN, JOEL CORTES TUCKER DESMOND, Hamza Doost; Court Reporter:\nBryan Wayne; Defense Attorney: 1-John P. Pierce, 3-Kevin Wilson, 4-Barry Coburn, 5-Shray Sharma, 6-Addy R. Schmitt, 10-Dwight E.\nCrawley, 11-George A. Dale, 14-Eugene V. Gorokhov; US Attorney: Kevin L. Rosenberg; Pretrial Officer: LaKeisha Forbes. (dot)\n(Entered: 06/20/2025)\n06/22/2025 159 Memorandum in Opposition by USA as to TUCKER DESMOND re 151 MOTION to Modify Conditions of Release (Rosenberg, Kevin)\n(Entered: 06/22/2025)\n06/23/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly: Motion Hearing as to KUNAL MEHTA (6) held on 6/23/2025 re\n144 MOTION for Reconsideration re 137 Order on Motion for Review,, Order on Motion to Stay,,,,,, Order on Motion for\nReconsideration, Motion to Re-Open Detention Hearing filed by KUNAL MEHTA. Heard and taken under advisement. Bond Status of\nDefendant: COMMITTED/COMMITMENT ISSUED; Court Reporter: Sonja Reeves; Defense Attorney: Addy R. Schmitt; US Attorney:\nKevin L. Rosenberg; Pretrial Officer: Britney Dahlkoetter;Witnesses: Karan Mehta. (dot) (Entered: 06/24/2025)\n06/25/2025 160 REPLY TO OPPOSITION to Motion by TUCKER DESMOND re 151 MOTION to Modify Conditions of Release (Gorokhov, Eugene)\n(Entered: 06/25/2025)\n06/26/2025 161 ORDER Setting Conditions of Release as to HAMZA DOOST (4) Personal Recognizance. Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on\n6/26/25. (dot) (Entered: 06/26/2025)\n06/26/2025 162 SUPPLEMENT by USA as to KUNAL MEHTA Supplemental Information for Court's Consideration (Rosenberg, Kevin) (Entered:\n06/26/2025)\n06/27/2025 163 MEMORANDUM OPINION & ORDER denying 144 Motion for Reconsideration as to KUNAL MEHTA (6). Signed by Judge Colleen\nKollar-Kotelly on 6/27/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 06/27/2025)\n06/27/2025 164 MEMORANDUM OPINION & ORDER granting in part and denying in part 151 Motion to Modify Conditions of Release as to\nTUCKER DESMOND (14). Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 6/27/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 06/27/2025)\n07/15/2025 166 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Joseph D. King appearing for CODY DEMIRTAS (King, Joseph) (Entered: 07/15/2025)\n07/16/2025 167 NOTICE OF ATTORNEY APPEARANCE: Robert A. Feitel appearing for ETHAN YARALLY (Feitel, Robert) (Entered: 07/16/2025)\n07/16/2025 Arrest of CODY DEMIRTAS (8) in Dulles, VA. (znjb) (Entered: 07/16/2025)\n07/16/2025 168 Arrest Warrant Returned Executed on 7/16/2025 as to CODY DEMIRTAS (8). (znjb) (Entered: 07/16/2025)\n07/16/2025 ORAL MOTION for Speedy Trial by CODY DEMIRTAS (8). (zltp) (Entered: 07/16/2025)\n07/16/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Matthew J. Sharbaugh: Return on Arrest Warrant/Initial\nAppearance/Arraignment as to CODY DEMIRTAS (8) as to Count 1,2 held on 7/16/2025. Plea of Not Guilty entered as to all counts. The\nCourt advised the Government of its Due Process Obligations under Rule 5(f). Government did not seek detention. Oral Motion by the\nGovernment for Speedy Trial as to CODY DEMIRTAS (8); heard and granted. Speedy Trial Excluded from 7/16/2025 to 8/28/2025 in the\nInterest of Justice (XT). Status Conference set for 8/28/2025 at 1:30 PM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-\nKotelly. Bond Status of Defendant: Defendant Released/Release Issued; Court Reporter: FTR-GOLD; FTR Time Frame: CTRM 7:\n[3:30:53 - 3:46:20]; Defense Attorney: Joseph King; US Attorney: Timothy Visser for Kevin Rosenberg; Pretrial Officer: Shania Fennell.\n(zltp) (Entered: 07/16/2025)\n07/16/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to CODY DEMIRTAS (8): As required by Rule 5(f), the United States is ordered to produce all exculpatory\nevidence to the defendant pursuant to Brady v. Maryland and its progeny. Not doing so in a timely manner may result in sanctions,\nincluding exclusion of evidence, adverse jury instructions, dismissal of charges and contempt proceedings. Signed by Magistrate Judge\nMatthew J. Sharbaugh on 7/16/2025. (znjb) (Entered: 07/17/2025)\n07/16/2025 171 ORDER Setting Conditions of Release as to CODY DEMIRTAS (8) Personal Recognizance/HISP. Signed by Magistrate Judge Matthew J.\nSharbaugh on 7/16/2025. (Attachment: #1 Appearance Bond) (znjb) (Entered: 07/17/2025)\n07/22/2025 172 Unopposed MOTION to Appoint Coordinating Discovery Attorney for CJA Panel Attorneys by EVAN TANGEMAN. (Attachments: # 1\nText of Proposed Order)(Crawley, Dwight) Modified to remove incorrect linked defendants on 7/23/2025 (zstd). (Entered: 07/22/2025)\n07/24/2025 175 ORDER as to ALL DEFENDANTS granting the 172 Unopposed Motion to Appoint Coordinating Discovery Attorney for CJA Panel\nAttorneys filed by EVAN TANGEMAN (10). Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 07/24/2025. (lcckk1) (Entered: 07/24/2025)\n07/25/2025 Arrest of ETHAN YARALLY (7) in Sterling, VA. (znjb) (Entered: 07/25/2025)\n07/25/2025 176 Arrest Warrant Returned Executed on 7/25/2025 as to ETHAN YARALLY (7). (znjb) (Entered: 07/25/2025)\n07/25/2025 MINUTE ORDER as to ETHAN YARALLY (7): As required by Rule 5(f), the United States is ordered to produce all exculpatory\nevidence to the defendant pursuant to Brady v. Maryland and its progeny. Not doing so in a timely manner may result in sanctions,\nincluding exclusion of evidence, adverse jury instructions, dismissal of charges and contempt proceedings. Signed by Magistrate Judge\nMatthew J. Sharbaugh on 7/25/2025. (znjb) (Entered: 07/25/2025)\n07/25/2025 ORAL MOTION for Speedy Trial by USA as to ETHAN YARALLY. (zltp) (Entered: 07/28/2025)\n07/25/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Magistrate Judge Matthew J. Sharbaugh: Return on Arrest Warrant/Initial\nAppearance/Arraignment as to ETHAN YARALLY as to Count 1,2 held on 7/25/2025. Plea of Not Guilty entered as to all counts. The\nCourt advised the Government of its Due Process Obligations under Rule 5(f). Government did not seek detention. Oral Motion by the\nGovernment for Speedy Trial as to ETHAN YARALLY (7); heard and granted. Speedy Trial Excluded from 7/25/2025 to 8/28/2025 in the\nInterest of Justice (XT). Status Conference set for 8/28/2025 at 2:30 PM in Courtroom 28A- In Person before Judge Colleen Kollar-\nKotelly. Bond Status of Defendant: Defendant Release/Release Issued; Court Reporter: FTR Gold; FTR Time Frame: CTRM 7: [2:41:36 -\n2:59:22]; Defense Attorney: Robert Feitel; US Attorney: Liz Aloi; Pretrial Officer: Britney Dahlkoetter. (zltp) (Entered: 07/28/2025)\n07/25/2025 178 ORDER Setting Conditions of Release as to ETHAN YARALLY (7) Personal Recognizance. Signed by Magistrate Judge Matthew J.\nSharbaugh on 7/25/2025. (Attachments: # 1 Appearance Bond) (zltp) (Entered: 07/28/2025)\n07/30/2025 NOTICE OF HEARING as to JOEL CORTES (11): Plea Agreement Hearing set for 7/31/2025 at 10:00 AM in Courtroom 28A- In Person\nbefore Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. (dot) (Entered: 07/30/2025)\n07/31/2025 179 Unopposed MOTION to Withdraw as Attorney by Alan Eisner and Dmitry Gorin. by KUNAL MEHTA. (Eisner, Alan) (Entered:\n07/31/2025)\n07/31/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly: Defendant sworn for the Plea Hearing. Plea Agreement Hearing\nas to JOEL CORTES (11) held on 7/31/2025. Plea entered by JOEL CORTES (11), Guilty as to Count 1 of the Indictment. JOEL CORTES\nNot Guilty on Count 3. DEFERRAL TO PROBATION OFFICE of Presentence Investigation Report as to JOEL CORTES. Joint Status\nReport due 10/31/2025 proposing dates for sentencing. Bond Status of Defendant: Personal Recognizance; Court Reporter: Lorraine\nHerman; Defense Attorney: George A. Dale; US Attorney: Kevin L. Rosenberg. (dot) (Entered: 07/31/2025)\n07/31/2025 180 WAIVER of Trial by Jury as to JOEL CORTES (11). Approved by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 7/31/25. (dot) (Entered: 07/31/2025)\n07/31/2025 181 STATEMENT OF OFFENSE IN SUPPORT OF GUILTY PLEA by USA as to JOEL CORTES (11). (dot) (Entered: 07/31/2025)\n07/31/2025 182 PLEA AGREEMENT as to JOEL CORTES (11). (dot) (Entered: 07/31/2025)\n08/01/2025 185 TRANSCRIPT OF 6/20/25 STATUS HEARING in case as to MALONE LAM, MARLON FERRO, HAMZA DOOST, CONOR\nFLANSBURG, KUNAL MEHTA, EVAN TANGEMAN, JOEL CORTES, TUCKER DESMOND before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly\nheld on June 20, 2025; Page Numbers: 1-37. Date of Issuance: 8/1/2025. Court Reporter: Bryan A. Wayne. Transcripts may be ordered by\nsubmitting the Transcript Order Form\n\nFor the first 90 days after this filing date, the transcript may be viewed at the courthouse at a public terminal or purchased from the court\nreporter referenced above. After 90 days, the transcript may be accessed via PACER. Other transcript formats, (multi-page, condensed, CD\nor ASCII) may be purchased from the court reporter.\n\nNOTICE RE REDACTION OF TRANSCRIPTS: The parties have twenty-one days to file with the court and the court reporter any\nrequest to redact personal identifiers from this transcript. If no such requests are filed, the transcript will be made available to the public\nvia PACER without redaction after 90 days. The policy, which includes the five personal identifiers specifically covered, is located on our\nwebsite at www.dcd.uscourts.gov.\n\nRedaction Request due 8/22/2025. Redacted Transcript Deadline set for 9/1/2025. Release of Transcript Restriction set for 10/30/2025.\n(Wayne, Bryan) (Entered: 08/01/2025)\n08/04/2025 MINUTE ORDER granting 179 Motion to Withdraw as Attorney. Alan Eisner and Dmitry Gorin withdrawn from case as to KUNAL\nMEHTA (6). Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 8/1/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 08/04/2025)\n08/22/2025 187 ORDER as to conditions of release for Defendant HAMZA DOOST (4). Signed by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 8/22/2025. (lcckk3)\n(Entered: 08/22/2025)\n08/25/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly: Defendant sworn for the Plea Hearing. Plea Agreement Hearing\nas to HAMZA DOOST (4) held on 8/25/2025. DEFERRAL TO PROBATION OFFICE of Presentence Investigation Report as to HAMZA\nDOOST. Plea entered by HAMZA DOOST (4), Guilty as to Count 1. Not Guilty on Counts 3. Ex parte Status Report by the Government\ndue by 11/26/2025. Bond Status of Defendant: Personal Recognizance; Court Reporter: Tim Miller; Defense Attorney: Barry Coburn; US\nAttorney: Kevin L. Rosenberg. (dot) (Entered: 08/25/2025)\n08/25/2025 188 WAIVER of Trial by Jury as to HAMZA DOOST (4). Approved by Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly on 8/25/25. (dot) (Entered: 08/25/2025)\n08/25/2025 189 STATEMENT OF OFFENSE by USA as to HAMZA DOOST (4). (dot) (Entered: 08/25/2025)\n08/25/2025 190 PLEA AGREEMENT as to HAMZA DOOST (4). (dot) (Entered: 08/25/2025)\n08/27/2025 196 ORDER as to CODY DEMIRTAS (8) confirming the Government's disclosure obligations under Brady v. Maryland. Signed by Judge\nColleen Kollar-Kotelly on 8/27/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 08/27/2025)\n08/27/2025 197 ORDER as to ETHAN YARALLY (7) confirming the Government's disclosure obligations under Brady v. Maryland. Signed by Judge\nColleen Kollar-Kotelly on 8/27/2025. (lcckk3) (Entered: 08/27/2025)\n08/28/2025 Minute Entry for proceedings held before Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly: Status Conference as to MALONE LAM (1), MARLON FERRO\n(3), CONOR FLANSBURG (5), KUNAL MEHTA (6), EVAN TANGEMAN (10) held on 8/28/2025. Excludable started as to MALONE\nLAM, MARLON FERRO, CONOR FLANSBURG, KUNAL MEHTA, EVAN TANGEMAN. Defendant Malone Lam asserted his right to\na Speedy Trial, the Court will make a ruling. Defendants FERRO, FLANSBURG, MEHTA, TANGEMAN, Speedy Trial (XT) is tolled in\nthe Interest of Justice from 8/28/2025 to 10/16/2025. Status Conference set for 10/16/2025 at 2:00 PM in Courtroom 28A- In Person\nbefore Judge Colleen Kollar-Kotelly. Bond Status of Defendants: MARLON FERRO, CONOR FLANSBURG, EVAN TANGEMAN on\nPersonal Recognizance; MALONE LAM and KUNAL MEHTA are Committed/Commitment Issued; Court Reporter: Janice Dickman;\nDefense Attorney: 1-John P. Pierce, 3-Kevin E. Wilson, 5-Shry Shaima, 6-Abby R. Schmitt, 10-Dwight E. Crawley; US Attorney: Kevin\nL. Rosenberg. (d"
